   FCC Commissioner Michael J. Copps Commissioner
   Michael J. Copps

   Nominated May 1, 2001; confirmed May 25, 2001; sworn in May 31, 2001.
   Copps served until January 2001 as Assistant Secretary of Commerce for
   Trade Development at the U.S. Department of Commerce, where he was
   previously Deputy Assistant Secretary of Commerce for Basic Industries.
   Copps came to Washington in 1970, joining the staff of Senator Ernest
   Hollings (D-SC) and serving for over a dozen years as Chief of Staff.
   He has also held positions at Collins and Aikman Corporation and the
   American Meat Institute. Before coming to Washington, Copps was a
   professor of U.S. History at Loyola University of the South. Copps
   received a B.A. from Wofford College and earned a Ph.D. from the
   University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.
     * Confirmation Press Release

